parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seatbelt system can lead to improper restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt light comes on
the chime rings when the seatbelt is fastened
the seatbelt jams or sticks
the seatbelt is hard to release
the seatbelt fails to retract properly
the motorized seatbelt fails
the warning light goes on when the seatbelt is latched.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dealer Failure to Correct Recall Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealer to correct the recall issue can lead to continued operation of the vehicle with a faulty automatic seatbelt system, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealer refuses to correct recall problem
dealer does not have parts available to repair the vehicle
dealer fails to advise customer of part unavailability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The discoloration of the plastic headlight lenses can cause the light to be very dim, reducing visibility while driving at night, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlight lenses turn yellow or milky
glazed appearance
dim light output
reduced visibility while driving at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the flasher unit can cause the turn signals to malfunction, leading to confusion for other drivers and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Turn signals do not function
turn signals function erratically
hazard lights do not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out or faulty front wheel bearings can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents. Additionally, the noise and vibration caused by faulty bearings can be a distraction to the driver, further increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: Noise from the front end
grinding or growling sounds when turning or driving
vibration in the steering wheel or seat
uneven tire wear
dragging or pulling to one side when driving
doors dragging when parking on uneven surfaces.
